==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suppositive
<hw>Sup*pos"i*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>suppositif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Including or implying supposition, or
hypothesis; supposed.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Sup*pos"i*tive*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <au>Hammond.</au></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suppositive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suppositive
<hw>Sup*pos"i*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A word denoting or implying
supposition, as the words <xex>if</xex>, <xex>granting</xex>,
<xex>provided</xex>, etc.</def> <rj><au>Harris.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suppositor</ent>⟦br⟧
